{
  "doc_id": "10373",
  "text": "In dimension n = 3, Perelman [CITATION_1] claimed that the Bryant soliton is the only complete noncompact, κ-noncollapsed, gradient steady soliton with positive sectional curvature. Recently, Brendle has affirmed this conjecture of Perelman (see [CITATION_2] ; and also [CITATION_3] for an extension to the higher dimensional case). On the other hand, for n ≥ 4, Cao-Chen [CITATION_4] and Catino-Mantegazza [CITATION_5] proved independently, and using different methods, that any n-dimensional complete noncompact locally conformally flat gradient steady Ricci soliton (M n , g ij , f ) is either flat or isometric to the Bryant soliton (the method of Cao-Chen [CITATION_6] also applies to the case of dimension n = 3). In addition, Bach-flat gradient steady solitons (with positive Ricci curvature) for all n ≥ 3 [CITATION_7] and half-conformally flat ones for n = 4 [CITATION_8] have been classified respectively.",
